sentences: Ivan Guimarães Lins (born  June 16, 1945) is a Latin Grammy-winning Brazilian musician.
Ivan Guimarães Lins (born  June 16, 1945) is a Latin Grammy-winning Brazilian musician.
He has been an active performer and songwriter of Brazilian popular music (MPB) and jazz for over thirty years.
His first hit, "Madalena", was recorded by Elis Regina in 1970.
"Love Dance", a hit in 1989, is one of the most recorded songs in musical history.
He spent several years in Boston, Massachusetts, while his father, a naval engineer, continued graduate studies at M.I.T., studied at the Military College in Rio.
Ivan Lins currently resides in Rio de Janeiro.
He recorded in English for Reprise/Warner Bros. Records in the early 1990s.
Lins appeared as a guest performer on the albums Dois Mundos (1998) and Recorded in Rio (2003) by the Dutch artist Josee Koning.

Lins guested on American artist Jane Monheit's album Surrender (2007), which includes his composition "Rio de Maio".
Jazz reporter and music critic David Adler reported Lins's October 2000 Carnegie Hall concert performance and tribute to him.
Lins maintains an active touring schedule, including a 2003 appearance at the Blue Note in New York City.

In 2005, he won two Latin Grammy Awards; Album of the Year and Best MPB (Música popular brasileira) Album for Cantando Histórias.
